  "text": "Conditional Random Fields (CRFs) [CITATION_1] ) are global discriminative learning algorithms for problems with structured output spaces, such as dependency parsing. For dependency parsing, CRFs would define the conditional probability of a dependency graph T for a sentence x as a globally nor-malized log-linear model,",
